properties.description:
Brisbane Fiesta Latina is a Culture, Food & Music Festival organised by Latin American Community of Australia (LACA QLD) to celebrate and share Latin-American culture with the wider community in Queensland.

BFL engages people from all age groups, abilities and diverse cultural backgrounds by offering a significant range of activities including culinary delicacies, varied musical and artistic performances from different countries in Latin America and a range of activities for kids and younger generations.

properties.subject: Cinematic Film Buffs Unite!
properties.location: Queensland Performing Arts Centre (QPAC), South Brisbane
properties.description:
Lights, Camera, Action! Cinematic is back for a fifth year of film favourites with conductor and host Nicholas Buc. Whether you’re a fan of sci-fi, itching for adventure, or ready for romance, there’s something for you in our 2024 lineup. Soar with the epic space odyssey of Hans Zimmer’s Interstellar and feel the bloom of a tender romance with Dario Marianelli’s soul-stirring accompaniment to Pride and Prejudice. With iconic themes from Forrest Gump, Batman, Downtown Abbey and many more, this is a guaranteed great time for the whole family. As always, our musicians will perform in costume, making this concert a riot of colour and characters. Grab some popcorn, kick back, and relive your favourite movie moments live in the Concert Hall.

Queensland Symphony Orchestra is proudly supported by Brisbane City Council.
properties.venue: Queensland Performing Arts Centre (QPAC), South Brisbane
properties.venueaddress: Queensland Performing Arts Centre, Cnr Melbourne and Grey Street, South Brisbane
properties.bookings: Bookings required. To book, visit Queensland Symphony Orchestra. Single tickets are on sale from 9am Wednesday 22 November 2023.

properties.subject: The Dark Side of the Moon Planetarium Experience
properties.location: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.description:
Pink Floyd’s iconic album ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’, originally released in March 1973, turns 50, and what more fitting a place to celebrate it and experience it than in a Planetarium, through the music set to visuals. With the help of modern technology, the idea of a show combining breath-taking views of the solar system and beyond, played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon in surround sound, has been embraced by the band. NSC Creative have led the visual production efforts, working closely with Pink Floyd’s long time creative collaborator Aubrey Powell from Hipgnosis.

Each song has a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. A truly immersive and all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.
properties.venue: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.venueaddress: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, 152 Mt Coot-tha Road, Mt Coot-tha
properties.bookings:
Click HERE to book any available 2024 session This show features strobe effects, mature themes and explicit language. Not recommended for children. FAQ
How long will this show be available? This show will run until December 2024 Why is this show not recommended for children? This show features a full play through of The Dark Side Of The Moon album. While there is no inappropriate visual content, the audio track does feature mature themes and explicit language. Children may attend if accompanied by an adult. Concession tickets may be purchased for children at the discretion of accompanying adults. Is there a waitlist for sold out shows? There is no waitlist for sold out shows. If tickets become available due to cancellations, they will be listed online via the booking link for 2024 shows. Is the venue wheelchair accessible? Yes, the Cosmic Skydome is fully wheelchair accessible.
properties.parentevent: The Dark Side of the Moon experience

properties.subject: Classic Encore
properties.description:
The AusOriental Inc.'s 10th anniversary concert, Classic Encore will be held to commemorate a decade of success, express gratitude to supporters, and showcase growth and progress over the years.

This concert showcases different forms of performance such as music, dancing, singing, drama, cheongsam catwalk, calligraphy and embroidery.

Over 160 performers and 9 local arts organisations will come together in a tribute to the organisation’s journey, highlighting its contributions to foster community, harmony and unity through the power of music. SunPAC is proudly supported by Brisbane City Council. For more information, please visit the SunPAC website.
properties.venueaddress: SunPAC, 470 McCullough Street, Macgregor
properties.bookings: Bookings required. To book, visit SunPAC.

properties.subject: ABBA theme Silent Disco Walking Tour
properties.description:
Guru Dudu's original Silent Disco Walking Tours are bringing their sell-out Abba tour to Brisbane!

Think Flash-mob meets Flashdance. Part comedy, part dance, part uplifting Brisbane city tour - all fun!

Our Silent Disco Walking Tours are a unique way to explore Brisbane city.

Join our dynamic host Rebel Yell, as she leads you on a magical journey of play, love, laughter & all-round good times, where everyone wears headphones (supplied) & we dance-walk-play our way through the city sharing a private soundscape, spontaneous dance-offs & special moments that enliven crowds wherever we go.

Featuring charismatic, professional guides, Fun, high-vibe Abba hits that everyone loves & faves from the 70s and 80's, Hilarious interactive commentary & Iconic city moments.
properties.venueaddress: Reddacliff Place, 266 George Street, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: Bookings required via the Guru Dudu website. Our award-winning tours often sell out, so grab your friends & join the fun!

properties.description:
Riverside at the Garden markets is a great way to spend your Sunday in the heart of the Brisbane CBD at the City Botanic Gardens.

For over 30 years, Brisbane’s Riverside Markets have been a popular gathering place for locals and tourists. Come and check out the range of art and fashion under the Queensland sun.

Live music every morning, and great international food and coffee. Come for breakfast, stay for the fantastic atmosphere.

properties.subject: Lord Mayor's City Hall Concerts - Tribute to Buddy Holly
properties.description:
Lord Mayor's City Hall Concerts present a Tribute to Buddy Holly.

The Australian Buddy Holly Show is an entertaining tribute to one of the pioneers of rock n roll. Starring Kris Knight who brings Buddy back to life, accompanied by his four-piece band of drums, guitar, stand up bass, keyboard and saxophone.

Kris has performed around the world, and also regularly guest entertains on luxury cruise ships, including Princess, Oceanic and Celebrity lines. This 60-minute show features Buddy's hits including 'Oh Boy', 'Rave On', 'That'll Be The Day', as well as beautiful ballads like 'Raining In My Heart', 'True Love Ways', and 'Everyday'.

This is real old time rock n roll!

This Lord Mayor's City Hall Concert is produced by Salubrious Productions.
properties.venueaddress: Brisbane City Hall, 64 Adelaide Street, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: No bookings required.

properties.subject: Troye Sivan - Something To Give Each Other Tour
properties.description:
In an announcement that is sure to thrill fans across Australia, Troye Sivan has unveiled dates for his highly anticipated Something To Give Each Other tour this November. After selling out arenas across Europe, the exploding pop sensation will light up stages in Adelaide, Melbourne, Brisbane, and Sydney, promising unforgettable performances in support of his critically acclaimed and globally celebrated album.

The tour kicks off on Tuesday 19 November at The Drive in Adelaide, followed by a night at Melbourne’s iconic Sidney Myer Music Bowl on Thursday 21 November. Brisbane fans will get their chance to see Sivan live on Tuesday 26 November at Riverstage, before he wraps up the tour with a performance at the Sydney Opera House Forecourt on Thursday 28 November.
properties.venueaddress: Riverstage, Gardens Point Road, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: Tickets can be purchased via the Ticketmaster website.

properties.subject: Gathering presents Nunukul Yuggera Aboriginal Dancers
properties.description:
Gathering presents Nunukul Yuggera Aboriginal Dancers.

The Nunukul Yuggera Aboriginal Dancers have been in existence for over 25 years, travelling the world extensively showcasing Traditional Aboriginal culture through song, dance and other various forms of cultural expression. They have performed alongside some of the world's greatest performers and cultural ambassadors. 

Be sure to come down to the Queen Street Mall stage between 12 noon to 1pm, and join Nunukul Yuggera Aboriginal Dancers for this free interactive and cultural performance. 

This Gathering event is produced by Cre8tive Nations.

properties.subject: An Australian Army Band CHRISTMAS
properties.description:
Join the Australian Army Band Brisbane as they present a concert celebrating this most wonderful time of the year at the SunPAC Performing Arts Theatre on the 28th November. Featuring our exciting vocalists and the 22-piece ensemble performing a selection of Christmas favourites both old and new, we look forward to welcoming you to SunPAC for a memorable Christmas concert.

Since its formation in 1949, the Australian Army Band Brisbane has enjoyed a reputation throughout Queensland for its musical and ceremonial excellence. Brisbane’s Army Band supports the Australian Army and Australian Defence Force units throughout South East Queensland. The Band regularly supports commemorative activities such as Anzac Day and also performs for the wider community; appearing at public events, major concerts, balls and charity fundraisers. Band members have deployed both domestically and internationally on operations.

The Band is a traditional big-band line up of saxophones, trumpets, trombones and rhythm section, complemented by exciting vocalists. Repertoire ranges from traditional sounds of the big band era, through to arrangements of contemporary rock and pop hits. Enjoying high acclaim wherever they perform, the Australian Army Band Brisbane is a great asset for the State of Queensland and for the Australian Army.

SunPAC is proudly supported by Brisbane City Council. For more information, please visit the SunPAC website.

properties.subject: The Dark Side of the Moon Planetarium Experience
properties.location: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.description:
Pink Floyd’s iconic album ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’, originally released in March 1973, turns 50, and what more fitting a place to celebrate it and experience it than in a Planetarium, through the music set to visuals. With the help of modern technology, the idea of a show combining breath-taking views of the solar system and beyond, played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon in surround sound, has been embraced by the band. NSC Creative have led the visual production efforts, working closely with Pink Floyd’s long time creative collaborator Aubrey Powell from Hipgnosis.

Each song has a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. A truly immersive and all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.
properties.venue: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.venueaddress: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, 152 Mt Coot-tha Road, Mt Coot-tha
properties.bookings:
Click HERE to book any available 2024 session This show features strobe effects, mature themes and explicit language. Not recommended for children. FAQ
How long will this show be available? This show will run until December 2024 Why is this show not recommended for children? This show features a full play through of The Dark Side Of The Moon album. While there is no inappropriate visual content, the audio track does feature mature themes and explicit language. Children may attend if accompanied by an adult. Concession tickets may be purchased for children at the discretion of accompanying adults. Is there a waitlist for sold out shows? There is no waitlist for sold out shows. If tickets become available due to cancellations, they will be listed online via the booking link for 2024 shows. Is the venue wheelchair accessible? Yes, the Cosmic Skydome is fully wheelchair accessible.

properties.subject: Romania Day 2024
properties.description:
Let's celebrate together Romania Day on 30 November 2024.

This day and night we will commemorate the effort and sacrifice to realise a centuries old dream of Romanians of The Great Union and the formation of National Romanian State on 1 December 1918. The festivities will start with a free entry Fair organised on the lawn of Capt. Burke Park, Kangaroo Point from 12pm to 6pm.

From 6:30pm important landmarks in Brisbane will be lit up in Romanian flag colours: Red-Yellow-Blue including Victoria Bridge, Story Bridge and Breakfast Creek Bridge, offering the perfect backdrop for photos with a "Romanian" flavour. A community bus will offer a limited number of seats for those who would like to take the tour starting at 6:30pm from Capt. Burke carpark.

Don't miss Brisbane River lit up in celebration! 

This event is proudly sponsored by Brisbane City Council.

properties.subject: Conquer NF in Colour
properties.description:
Whether you're a seasoned runner or simply looking for a fun day out with friends, family or workmates, Conquer NF in Colour offers an unforgettable experience for people of all ages and abilities!

Choose your distance—2km, 4km, or 10km—and immerse yourself in an event filled with colour explosions, cool water gauntlet, live music, delicious food trucks, interactive games, and a lively party atmosphere that promises endless fun for everyone!

This event raises awareness for people living with tumours, or more specifically a condition called neurofibromatosis (NF). You do not have to have a connection to NF to enjoy this event however, it is designed with families of all shapes, sizes and abilities in mind.

SRCB is a not-for-profit community band established to give community members an opportunity to make music together in a fun and educational approach, and to provide the wider community with entertaining and accessible performances.

properties.subject: The Dark Side of the Moon Planetarium Experience
properties.location: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.description:
Pink Floyd’s iconic album ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’, originally released in March 1973, turns 50, and what more fitting a place to celebrate it and experience it than in a Planetarium, through the music set to visuals. With the help of modern technology, the idea of a show combining breath-taking views of the solar system and beyond, played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon in surround sound, has been embraced by the band. NSC Creative have led the visual production efforts, working closely with Pink Floyd’s long time creative collaborator Aubrey Powell from Hipgnosis.

Each song has a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. A truly immersive and all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.
properties.venue: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.venueaddress: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, 152 Mt Coot-tha Road, Mt Coot-tha
properties.bookings:
Click HERE to book any available 2024 session This show features strobe effects, mature themes and explicit language. Not recommended for children. FAQ
How long will this show be available? This show will run until December 2024 Why is this show not recommended for children? This show features a full play through of The Dark Side Of The Moon album. While there is no inappropriate visual content, the audio track does feature mature themes and explicit language. Children may attend if accompanied by an adult. Concession tickets may be purchased for children at the discretion of accompanying adults. Is there a waitlist for sold out shows? There is no waitlist for sold out shows. If tickets become available due to cancellations, they will be listed online via the booking link for 2024 shows. Is the venue wheelchair accessible? Yes, the Cosmic Skydome is fully wheelchair accessible.

properties.description:
The Brookfield Show Society “Bush Christmas” in 2024 on Friday 6 December at 4pm. The free event provides the community with an opportunity to come together and celebrate Christmas and the end of another year.

Held at the Showgrounds, families will be able to sit at the bar or on the terraces, enjoy some musical entertainment and buy a bite to eat. There will also be free rides and activities for the kids, and a special visitor from the North Pole!

properties.subject: The Dark Side of the Moon Planetarium Experience
properties.location: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.description:
Pink Floyd’s iconic album ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’, originally released in March 1973, turns 50, and what more fitting a place to celebrate it and experience it than in a Planetarium, through the music set to visuals. With the help of modern technology, the idea of a show combining breath-taking views of the solar system and beyond, played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon in surround sound, has been embraced by the band. NSC Creative have led the visual production efforts, working closely with Pink Floyd’s long time creative collaborator Aubrey Powell from Hipgnosis.

Each song has a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. A truly immersive and all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.
properties.venue: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.venueaddress: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, 152 Mt Coot-tha Road, Mt Coot-tha
properties.bookings:
Click HERE to book any available 2024 session This show features strobe effects, mature themes and explicit language. Not recommended for children. FAQ
How long will this show be available? This show will run until December 2024 Why is this show not recommended for children? This show features a full play through of The Dark Side Of The Moon album. While there is no inappropriate visual content, the audio track does feature mature themes and explicit language. Children may attend if accompanied by an adult. Concession tickets may be purchased for children at the discretion of accompanying adults. Is there a waitlist for sold out shows? There is no waitlist for sold out shows. If tickets become available due to cancellations, they will be listed online via the booking link for 2024 shows. Is the venue wheelchair accessible? Yes, the Cosmic Skydome is fully wheelchair accessible.

properties.subject: Lord Mayor's Christmas Carols
properties.description:
The Lord Mayor's Christmas Carols returns bigger and better in 2024 to spread joy to the world with a dazzling evening of high kicks, high notes and hijinks.

Hosted by Queensland’s first lady of song Naomi Price, this world-class evening of entertainment features a breathtaking all-Australian line-up of superstars to be announced in November.

The Lord Mayor’s Christmas Carols is proudly ‘access all areas’ with Auslan interpretation, audio description, tactile tours, accessible viewing platform, dedicated Auslan area, low sensory zone, haptic vests and wristbands, and captions on screen.

Don’t miss this tree-mendous night for the whole family! Gates open at 4pm. Preshow entertainment from 6pm. Main event 7-9pm.

The Lord Mayor’s Christmas Carols proudly supports the Lord Mayor’s Charitable Trust.

For further event and venue information, visit our Lord Mayor's Christmas Carols page.

Carols live stream
The carols program will be live streamed by Channel Nine from Riverstage into Victoria Park, allowing more visitors to share in the magic of this event. Find out more about the free Victoria Park satellite event.
properties.venueaddress: Riverstage, Gardens Point Road, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: This event is now sold out.

properties.subject: Lord Mayor's Christmas Carols - Victoria Park Satellite Event
properties.description:
The Lord Mayor's Christmas Carols returns bigger and better in 2024 to spread joy to the world with a dazzling evening of high kicks, high notes and hijinks. The program will be live streamed by Channel Nine from Brisbane Riverstage into Victoria Park, allowing more visitors to share in the magic of this event.

Hosted by Queensland’s first lady of song, Naomi Price, this world-class evening of entertainment features a breathtaking all-Australian lineup of superstars, including Conrad Sewell, Ngaiire, Josh Pyke, Queensland Ballet, Jess Hitchcock, Emma Pask, Luke Kennedy, Fatai, Andy Cook, Dean Brady, and Waveney Yasso.

Join us on Victoria Park’s rolling green hills from 4.30pm and enjoy pre-show entertainment as the sun sets, including live performances by jazz entertainers SCAT.

Food trucks will be open from 4.30pm to purchase a selection of tasty sweet and savoury food and non-alcoholic drinks or you can pack your own picnic. Remember to pack a picnic blanket to enjoy the evening in comfort. Note, alcohol is not permitted at this event.

From 7pm, settle in under the stars for the live stream of the Lord Mayor’s Christmas Carols from Riverstage. The Lord Mayor’s Christmas Carols Victoria Park Satellite Event is a Brisbane City Council initiative, produced by City Parklands and The Little Red Company, broadcast by Nine Network, and proudly supporting the Lord Mayor’s Charitable Trust.

AccessibilityThe pre-show entertainment at Victoria Park will be Auslan interpreted and the live-streamed event from Riverstage will also offer Auslan interpretation with on-screen captions. For easy access, designated drop-off areas and accessible parking are available on Gilchrist Avenue. Note, the parkland includes sloped and uneven ground at the event site.Venue
Entry is via Gilchrist Avenue, Herston. While the venue provides a natural amphitheatre with tiered seating, we ask patrons to be mindful of line of sight and ask those who bring chairs to choose their location accordingly.

Getting to Victoria Park is easy. Visitors are encouraged to travel to the event by walking, cycling or public transport. The park is well serviced by buses via the Inner Northern Busway, with the nearest stop at Herston. Visit the Translink website for more information.

There is limited free parking available on the Victoria Park Sporting Fields off Gilchrist Ave. There will be a dedicated area on Gilchrist Avenue for ride share pick up/drop off. No event parking is available at the carpark off Herston Road. Paid parking is available at Cornerstone Parking Herston Road Car Park.
properties.venueaddress: Victoria Park / Barrambin, Central Parkland,
properties.bookings: This is a free event although capacity is limited and pre-registration is required via Oztix.

properties.subject: Bach's Christmas Oratorio A Festive Celebration - QLD Conservatorium Theatre
properties.description:
Celebrate the festive season with Bach’s sublime Christmas Oratorio. This expression of joy is the perfect close to the year. Conductor Benjamin Bayl has chosen a jubilant collection of Bach’s masterwork for this special performance. The sanctity of the nativity and the wonder of the Christmas season sing through pastoral woodwind and triumphant brass, as the conservatorium theatre becomes a poignant cathedral of sound. Exultant and divine, Bach’s holy offering is timeless. Soloists Sara Macliver, Stephanie Dillon, Paul McMahon and Shaun Brown are joined by the expressive qualities of the Brisbane Chamber Choir, in one of the most eloquent tributes to the festive season.

Queensland Symphony Orchestra is proudly supported by Brisbane City Council.
properties.cost: 2024 Single tickets are on sale from 9am Wednesday 22 November 2023.
properties.bookings: Bookings required. To book, visit Queensland Symphony Orchestra.

properties.subject: Riverside at the Gardens Markets
properties.description:
Riverside at the Garden markets is a great way to spend your Sunday in the heart of the Brisbane CBD at the City Botanic Gardens.

For over 30 years, Brisbane’s Riverside Markets have been a popular gathering place for locals and tourists. Come and check out the range of art and fashion under the Queensland sun.

Live music every morning, and great international food and coffee. Come for breakfast, stay for the fantastic atmosphere.

Follow Riverside at the Garden Markets on Instagram.

Visit the Riverside Markets website if you'd like to become a stall holder.

properties.bookings: No bookings required.

properties.subject: The Dark Side of the Moon Planetarium Experience
properties.location: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.description:
Pink Floyd’s iconic album ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’, originally released in March 1973, turns 50, and what more fitting a place to celebrate it and experience it than in a Planetarium, through the music set to visuals. With the help of modern technology, the idea of a show combining breath-taking views of the solar system and beyond, played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon in surround sound, has been embraced by the band. NSC Creative have led the visual production efforts, working closely with Pink Floyd’s long time creative collaborator Aubrey Powell from Hipgnosis.

Each song has a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. A truly immersive and all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.
properties.venue: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.venueaddress: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, 152 Mt Coot-tha Road, Mt Coot-tha
properties.bookings:
Click HERE to book any available 2024 session This show features strobe effects, mature themes and explicit language. Not recommended for children. FAQ
How long will this show be available? This show will run until December 2024 Why is this show not recommended for children? This show features a full play through of The Dark Side Of The Moon album. While there is no inappropriate visual content, the audio track does feature mature themes and explicit language. Children may attend if accompanied by an adult. Concession tickets may be purchased for children at the discretion of accompanying adults. Is there a waitlist for sold out shows? There is no waitlist for sold out shows. Yes, the Cosmic Skydome is fully wheelchair accessible.

properties.subject: Brisbane Bunya Lions Carols in the Park
properties.description:
The Brisbane Bunya Lions Club is hosting their annual “Carols in the Park” event on Saturday 14 December 2024.

The much-loved community show will be?held at Mitchelton Park on the?grounds?of?Wests Mitchelton Junior Rugby League Football Club and everyone in the local community is invited to attend.?

With free?entry, parking,?live entertainment,?free face painting, children’s activities and rides, this event?is perfect for all ages and?has been?attended?by?thousands since it began in 2015.

?There will be a huge stage with sound and lighting, a fantastic line up of entertainers including?the Fabulous Lemon Drops (for the kids!), AMMA School of Dance performers and a jam-packed line up of all your favourite Christmas Carols.?

And for the young ones, and the young at heart, Santa will visit to meet and greet with the children and will sit for family photos. All this followed by a spectacular fireworks display will end the evening.?

With easy access to rides, activities for the kids, dinner, drinks and dessert vendors, all visitors?are invited to?bring along picnic rugs and festival chairs to sit on?and?enjoy the evening?in comfort.?

There will be an array of Christmas market stalls in support of local artisans in jewellery, fashion, candles, toys, collectibles, art, plants, other quality items and children’s activities.

See you there!

This event is proudly supported by Brisbane City Council. For more information, please visit the event Facebook page.

properties.subject: Wallows
properties.description:
Frontier Touring is excited to announce the return of multi-Platinum alt-rock trio Wallows, bringing their biggest global headline tour thus far to arenas in Perth, Adelaide, Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane, Wellington and Auckland this December – the Model Tour 2024.

The tour news comes in celebration of the band’s highly anticipated third studio album, Model. The John Congleton-produced (St. Vincent, Sharon Van Etten) record arrives May 24 via Atlantic Records.

Wallows will kick off the Model World Tour with 38 dates across North America, Europe and the UK, making their debut performances at some of the world’s most famous venues including New York City’s Madison Square Garden and London’s Alexandra Palace. With their previous tour of AU/NZ in 2022 selling out fast, fans should not delay in grabbing tickets for these just-announced shows.

Wallows (composed of Dylan Minnette, Braeden Lemasters and Cole Preston) have been best friends since the age of 11. They began playing music together in the LA music program Join the Band almost two decades ago and haven’t stopped since. In March 2022, the band released their sophomore album, Tell Me That It’s Over, produced by 3x GRAMMY Award-winner Ariel Rechtshaid (Vampire Weekend, Haim, Adele).

TMTIO saw Wallows continuing on their ever-evolving journey of sonic exploration, fusing a vast array of musical ideas – from lo-fi post-punk and indie-folk to early ’90s dance-pop psychedelia – into their own one-of-a-kind creative vision. TMTIO marked the full-length follow-up to Wallows’ hugely popular 2019 debut album, Nothing Happens, produced by GRAMMY Award-winner John Congleton (St. Vincent, Sharon Van Etten). The album proved to be one of that year’s highest streamed debuts.

In the live space, Wallows have headlined sold out shows around the globe and have performed at marquee festivals such as Coachella, Lollapalooza, Reading and Leeds, and more.

properties.subject: Pub Choir's Christmas Fundraising Extravaganza
properties.description:
At the end of each year, people all around the world gather in December to celebrate and reflect upon the most important thing to have ever happened: Pub Choir’s Christmas Fundraising Extravaganza!

“This is the objective best event in history”, is a direct future quote from your mouth as you sit under the night sky at Brisbane’s Riverstage, surrounded by friends, all full of snacks and bursting with song. There will be a raffle. There will be an orchestra. It will feel very cathartic to yell a song together.

What is Pub Choir? An improvised, comedy music lesson that requires you to listen to the instructions, try your best, and to help the people around you. You will be led to musical glory by Pub Choir creator and everyone’s fave crackpot choirmistress, Astrid Jorgensen. Every kind of singing voice is welcome, even very bad ones.

Every cent of profit will go towards Women’s Legal Service Queensland, who are protecting vulnerable women and families at a really tough time of year. Think of this as a Christmas gift to your city: being nice to strangers, making music together, and giving cash to an organisation that makes Brisbane better.

This is an 18+, general admission show, and Auslan interpreted.

Note: Please be aware that this event will be filmed & photographed. By purchasing a ticket and attending this event, you are giving your consent to be filmed & photographed during this event.

properties.subject: The Dark Side of the Moon Planetarium Experience
properties.location: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.description:
Pink Floyd’s iconic album ‘The Dark Side Of The Moon’, originally released in March 1973, turns 50, and what more fitting a place to celebrate it and experience it than in a Planetarium, through the music set to visuals. With the help of modern technology, the idea of a show combining breath-taking views of the solar system and beyond, played out to 42 minutes of The Dark Side Of The Moon in surround sound, has been embraced by the band. NSC Creative have led the visual production efforts, working closely with Pink Floyd’s long time creative collaborator Aubrey Powell from Hipgnosis.

Each song has a different theme; some futuristically looking forward and some a retro acknowledgment to Pink Floyd’s visual history, all relating to a time and space experience, embracing up to the minute technology that only a Planetarium can offer. A truly immersive and all-encompassing surround sound and visual treat that will transcend reality and take you way beyond the realms of 2D experience.
properties.venue: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, Mt Coot-tha
properties.venueaddress: Sir Thomas Brisbane Planetarium, 152 Mt Coot-tha Road, Mt Coot-tha
properties.bookings:
Click HERE to book any available 2024 session This show features strobe effects, mature themes and explicit language. Not recommended for children. FAQ
How long will this show be available? This show will run until December 2024 Why is this show not recommended for children? This show features a full play through of The Dark Side Of The Moon album. While there is no inappropriate visual content, the audio track does feature mature themes and explicit language. Children may attend if accompanied by an adult. Concession tickets may be purchased for children at the discretion of accompanying adults. Is there a waitlist for sold out shows? There is no waitlist for sold out shows. If tickets become available due to cancellations, they will be listed online via the booking link for 2024 shows. Is the venue wheelchair accessible? Yes, the Cosmic Skydome is fully wheelchair accessible.
properties.parentevent: The Dark Side of the Moon experience

properties.subject: Dom Dolla
properties.description:
Untitled Group is thrilled to present Dom Dolla’s 2024 Australian Tour! These will mark Dom’s largest-ever Australian shows across Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane and Perth.

Hot off an incredible summer run, following two record-breaking sell-out shows at Melbourne’s Sidney Myer Music Bowl, and co-headlining ‘Spilt Milk festival’ nationally with Post Malone, Dom's meteoric rise continues in 2024. Dom broke international headlines with a surprise set at Beyond The Valley alongside Rufus Du Sol, secured an ARIA award for Best Dance Electronic Release, took out back-to-back spots #3 & #4 in `Triple J’s hottest 100, and received a Grammy nomination for his remix of Gorillaz “New Gold'' ft. Tame Impala & Bootie Brown. Following the rapid sell-out of his most recent Australian headline shows, we anticipate these tickets to go just as quickly.

Brace yourself for an explosive start to the next summer season!
properties.venueaddress: Riverstage, Gardens Point Road, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: Tickets can be purchased via Ticketmaster.

properties.subject: Gone Frolicking: Sandgate
properties.description:
Girls of all ages just want to have fun!

Did you dance when you were younger? Maybe you never had the chance? It’s never too late to (re)start! Dancing is fun and really good for us throughout life, so come frolic with like-minded people!

Hosted by pro-ageing dance captain Dr Anja Ali-Haapala, our events are joyful, pop music-loving dance workshops. Designed to accommodate diverse over 50s, our priorities are dancing safely, socially connecting and getting sassy on the dance floor. By the end of the session you will perform a beginner-level jazz dance to a pop song from the 70s or 80s with new friends.

Not up to scratch with your dance technique? It doesn’t matter! This isn’t a technique class. All you need is a little courage and we’ll take care of the rest!

properties.subject: IDLES
properties.description:
British rock outfit IDLES will make their highly-anticipated return to Australia in support of their new album, TANGK.

TANGK is the righteous and vibrant fifth album from madcap truth-seekers, IDLES. Pronounced “tank” with a whiff of the “g” - an onomatopoeic reference to the lashing way the band imagined their guitars sounding that has since grown into a sigil for living in love - the record is the band’s most ambitious and striking work yet. Where IDLES were once set on taking the world’s piss, squaring off with strong jaws against the perennially entitled, and exercising personal trauma in real time, they have arrived in this new act to offer the fruits of such perseverance: love, joy, and indeed gratitude for the mere opportunity of existence.

A radical sense of defiant empowerment radiates from TANGK, co-produced by Nigel Godrich, IDLES guitarist Mark Bowen, and Kenny Beats. Despite his reputation as an incendiary post-punk sparkplug, frontman Joe Talbot sings almost all the feelings inside these 10 songs with hard-earned soul, offering each lusty vow or solidarity plea as a bona fide pop song—that is, a thing for everyone to pass around and share, communal anthems intended for overcoming our grievance. Lead single “Dancer” stands as the throbbing and scuzzy highlight at the album’s center - rattling bass and ricocheting guitar giving Talbot space to talk about sweat and sex on the dancefloor. (You will spy LCD Soundsystem’s James Murphy and Nancy Whang here, too, singing.) It is lascivious and playful and positive, the ecstatic sound of at least a temporary fix. In the improvised hook, Talbot offers IDLES’ essential new mantra: “I give myself to you/As long as you move on the floor.”

He is singing about the rapture of a new relationship, but he is also singing about the special dynamic between IDLES and their fans, or IDLES and the world at large. This is a band’s vow to keep lifting and fighting for themselves and their listeners, to keep offering the grim persistence of joy and hope and love and wonder as long as that’s what anyone needs to survive. It is a love song the same way that TANGK is a love album—open to anyone who requires something to shout out loud in order to fend off any encroaching sense of the void, now or forever.

properties.subject: Benson Boone
properties.description:
With more than 1.9 billion global streams to his name, US-singer and songwriter Benson Boone is having a remarkable year. The ‘In The Stars’ star will perform five headline shows in Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane and Auckland in January 2025, when he brings his highly anticipated world down under. Originally scheduled for September 2024, with Boone’s stardom on a heady rise, dates have been rescheduled to January.

When he lands on our shores Boone is certain to touch more hearts than ever before, the 21-year-old winning fans worldwide with his single ‘Beautiful Things’ out now via Night Street Records/Warner Records. Generating tens of millions of streams globally, Boone was first discovered by Imagine Dragons frontman Dan Reynolds, who quickly signed him to his label Night Street Records. The singer made his first visit to Australia and New Zealand in October 2022, the Seattle native blowing away fans with his emotional vocals and powerful stage presence.

As one of music’s most exciting new artists, Benson Boone is a must-see. Don’t miss him live on stage in January!

properties.subject: Bad Omens
properties.description:
American band Bad Omens have announced their highly anticipated return to Australia in January 2025.

Supported by multimedia artist and visionary Poppy and alt-metal outfit House of Protection, Bad Omens will bring the Goodbye, Friend tour down the east coast of Australia.

Bad Omens are ready to entertain eager Australian fans once again, after their 2023 Knotfest appearances and sold-out tours around the rest of the world. Off the back of their latest LP Concrete Jungle [The OST] released this year and an experimental extension of their 2022 LP, The Death of Peace of Mind, the band has kept up appearances with select festival performances including Brazil’s KNOTFEST and a headline slot at California’s MAYHEM Festival. Coming up in November, Bad Omens will be supporting LINKIN PARK on their From Zero World Tour in Arlington, Texas.

properties.subject: Gone Frolicking: Wynnum
properties.description:
Girls of all ages just want to have fun!

Did you dance when you were younger? Maybe you never had the chance? It’s never too late to (re)start! Dancing is fun and really good for us throughout life, so come frolic with like-minded people!

Hosted by pro-ageing dance captain Dr Anja Ali-Haapala, our events are joyful, pop music-loving dance workshops. Designed to accommodate diverse over 50s, our priorities are dancing safely, socially connecting and getting sassy on the dance floor. By the end of the session you will perform a beginner-level jazz dance to a pop song from the 70s or 80s with new friends.

Not up to scratch with your dance technique? It doesn’t matter! This isn’t a technique class. All you need is a little courage and we’ll take care of the rest!

properties.subject: The Prodigy
properties.description:
Pioneers of the electronic music scene, The Prodigy, have announced their return to Australia in February 2025.

Presented by Astral People, Handsome Tours & Double J, they will be playing three shows at Sydney’s Hordern Pavilion, Brisbane’s Riverstage, and Melbourne’s Rod Laver Arena.

Returning five years after the tragic passing of the group’s vocalist Keith Flint, just weeks after they toured the country, the group comes armed with seven seminal albums, and a reputation as one of the world’s most visceral and incendiary live bands. Bringing together raves and metalheads to honour both their past and their present.

The “Godfathers of Rave” aka Liam Howlett, Keith Flint, and Maxim have solidified their status as legends in the music industry with a career spanning over three decades. The Prodigy are renowned for pioneering the big beat genre, blending elements of rave, techno, and industrial music. The group, initially featuring vocalist Keith Flint and MC Maxim, gained international acclaim with their debut album, Experience (1992). Their breakthrough came with the album Music for the Jilted Generation (1994), which showcased their innovative sound and rebellious spirit. The Prodigy's third album, The Fat of the Land (1997), solidified their status as electronic music legends, featuring hits like ‘Firestarter’ and ‘Breathe’, and topping charts worldwide.

Note: This event will include the use of strobe lights and/or lasers.
properties.venueaddress: Riverstage, Gardens Point Road, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: Tickets can be purchased via Ticketmaster Pre-sale tickets for The Prodigy will be available from Tuesday 27 Aug at 11am (local), with the general on-sale on Friday 30 August at 11am (local).

properties.subject: The Corrs
properties.description:
Back by popular demand, Irish Celtic infused pop icons, The Corrs are returning to Australia in February 2025 for three very special shows!

Gabriella Cilmi will join them for all shows with Bachelor Girl appearing in Brisbane and Sydney and as Rochford Winery Yarra Valley exclusive, The Corrs will be joined by very special guest, Delta Goodrem.

Australian fans of The Corrs are some of the most loyal in the world with the band achieving sales in excess of two million albums locally since debuting in1995 with Forgiven, Not Forgotten crashed into the charts and our hearts.

After stunning the 13,000 strong crowd at Hope Estate Hunter Valley for One Night Only in 2022, plus their follow up national tour in 2023 with sold out shows in Sydney and Melbourne, The Corrs are thrilled to return in 2025 bringing their music to fans in Brisbane, Sydney and Melbourne once again!

properties.subject: SIX60
properties.description:
After their regional Grassroots Tour earlier this year became the fastest sell-out tour in SIX60’s history, New Zealand’s biggest band is back, answering the call from fans who missed out. The SIX60 Grassroots City Edition Tour presented by Niche Productions and The Morningshift gives fans another chance to experience the band up close in a raw, intimate setting – this time outside at picturesque city venues that elevate the experience to a whole new level and allow a celebration of late-summer in Australia.

The SIX60 Grassroots Tour will see the band perform in four carefully selected locations over four Saturdays in February and March.

properties.bookings: Tickets can be purchased via Ticketmaster.

properties.subject: Fontaines D.C. with Wunderhorse
properties.description:
Handsome Tours are proud to present the highly anticipated return of Fontaines D.C. in 2025 in support of their newly released album ROMANCE.

Fontaines D.C.’s fourth album ROMANCE interrogates amorphous concepts of love and relationships, alienation and identity, fantasy and reality – all building to a central statement that Chatten sings of hauntingly, invitingly, on the opening track: “Maybe romance is a place”. It’s set to build on the success of the Dublin-made, now London-based band’s acclaimed 2022 album Skinty Fia, which reached number 1 in the UK and Irish album charts and saw the band receiving a host of accolades including “International Group of the Year” at the 2023 BRIT Awards.

properties.subject: Gone Frolicking: Grange
properties.description:
Girls of al ages just want to have fun!

Did you dance when you were younger? Maybe you never had the chance? It’s never too late to (re)start! Dancing is fun and really good for us throughout life, so come frolic with like-minded people!

Hosted by pro-ageing dance captain Dr Anja Ali-Haapala, our events are joyful, pop music-loving dance workshops. Designed to accommodate diverse over 50s, our priorities are dancing safely, socially connecting and getting sassy on the dance floor. By the end of the session you will perform a beginner-level jazz dance to a pop song from the 70s or 80s with new friends.

Not up to scratch with your dance technique? It doesn’t matter! This isn’t a technique class. All you need is a little courage and we’ll take care of the rest!
properties.bookings: Bookings required via Humanitix.

properties.subject: Khruangbin
properties.description:
They’re heralded as one of the USA’s finest live acts – a band unparalleled in groove. Now, Houston, Texas psych-funk trio Khruangbin return to Australia next summer with shows in Melbourne, Brisbane, and Sydney in February/March 2025 as part of their global A LA SALA tour.

Having recently wowed fans at European festivals such as Rock Werchter and Roskilde, bassist Laura Lee Ochoa, drummer Donald ‘DJ’ Johnson, Jr., and guitarist Mark ‘Marko’ Speer will return to Australia to celebrate their first album in four years: A LA SALA (“To the room” in Spanish). If 2020’s Mordechai was a party record that enhanced the band’s musical reputation, A LA SALA is the measured morning after. A gorgeously airy album made with minimal overdubs, A LA SALA scales Khruangbin down to scale up, a creative strategy with the future in mind.

Khruangbin launched the A LA SALA tour in April at Coachella, with sold out shows across US/Canada in May/June. With festival sets at Nos Alive (Lisbon), Latitude (Suffolk), Bilbao BBK (Spain) and Bonnaroo (US) on the itinerary, and European/UK dates in November, Khruangbin return to Australia in early 2025 for what promises to be some of the hottest shows this summer.

Joining Khruangbin as special guest at all shows and making their debut trip to Australia is acclaimed two-piece Hermanos Gutiérrez, the instrumental guitar duo of Swiss/Ecuadorian brothers Alejandro and Estevan Gutiérrez. The pair’s new album, Sonido Cósmico,  was released in June and produced by Dan Auerbach (The Black Keys). Brimming with Latin mystique and otherworldly guitar interplay that “shimmers with hallucinogenic energy” (Rolling Stone), the album is an odyssey through lush musical soundscapes, as heard on lead single ‘Barrio Hustle’.

properties.subject: NIKI Buzz World Tour
properties.description:
On Buzz, her songwriting remains as intimate as ever. In her initial sketches of songs for Buzz, NIKI took cues from other lane-paving women with confessional, honest lyricism soundtracked by guitars. “Joni Mitchell is my songwriting north star,” she says — and uncompromising feminist luminaries like Stevie Nicks, Carly Simon and Liz Phair. To match the wandering spirit of Buzz, NIKI cultivated her own elastic approach to guitar.

For NIKI, things have been happening progressively since she was a high schooler in Jakarta, Indonesia. As a student at an international academy, she cut her teeth scribbling lovesick poems in English class and performed acoustic guitar covers of American pop songs on YouTube. With a six-string in hand, and her family and classmates cheering her on from the audience, Nicole Zefanya then staked her claim to global stardom as NIKI.

And claim it she has - with over three billion streams worldwide, sold out shows on multiple continents, massive sets at festivals across the globe, front row seats at Paris Fashion Week, four songs on a Marvel film’s soundtrack, and some of the most phenomenal, confessional songs being released in 2024, NIKI has already established a veteran’s resume before the age of 25. Buzz reverberates with the hard-earned wisdom of a young woman who charges dauntlessly towards her dreams - but can still spare a laugh if she stumbles.

properties.bookings: Tickets purchased via Ticketmaster.

properties.subject: Alexisonfire with Underoath
properties.description:
Canadian hardcore luminaries Alexisonfire announce their Australian return for March 2025, alongside iconic US rockers Underoath and New Jersey punk four-piece Gel, in what will be an unmissable series of shows for local hard music lovers.

Alexisonfire was last in Australia in February 2023 touring Otherness, the band’s first album in over a decade. Admired by local audiences, on their ninth visit, the five-piece will perform songs from an enduring catalogue spanning more than twenty years.

The band’s legacy across Canada and the world cannot be overstated; from opening to Blink 182 at Toronto’s Rogers Centre Stadium in August, to announcing on the 2025 instalment of When We Were Young festival in Las Vegas, Alexisonfire continue to dominate.

properties.subject: New Order
properties.description:
Iconic synth-pop pioneers, New Order have today announced an Australian tour for March 2025.  The tour will see them perform all the biggest hits from their impressive four-decade, 10-album career on stages across Perth, Melbourne, Brisbane and Sydney in March 2025.  

Their first Australian tour since 2020, New Order will transform some of the country’s most beloved live music venues into synth-pop laser wonderlands. They hit RAC Arena (Perth) on March 5, Sidney Myer Music Bowl (Melbourne) on March 8, Riverstage (Brisbane) on March 11, and finishing up with two shows on the spectacular Sydney Opera House Forecourt on March 14 and 15.
properties.venueaddress: Riverstage, Gardens Point Road, Brisbane City
properties.bookings: Bookings required via Ticketmaster or Ticketek.

properties.subject: Kehlani - Crash World Tour
properties.description:
Kehlani will open your eyes, open your mind, and open your heart. For as blunt as she may be about life, longing, lust, and love, her music occupies an elevated state above even the best high yet accessible by simply listening.

The Bay Area-born two-time GRAMMY® Award-nominated multi-platinum songstress unlocks this place anytime she picks up a pen or grabs a microphone. Since 2014, her light has only continued to glow brighter. Thus far she’s picked up over twenty Gold and Platinum RIAA certifications, tallied 9 billion streams, and garnered a pair of GRAMMY® Award nominations in the categories of “Best Urban Contemporary Album'' for the gold-certified mixtape You Should Be Here and “Best R&B Performance” for the platinum single “Distraction.”

Beyond blockbuster collaborations with Cardi B, Justin Bieber, Post Malone, Burna Boy, Young Boy Never Broke Again, Calvin Harris, she has appeared on soundtracks such as Suicide Squad: The Album, The Fate of the Furious: The Album, and more. Along the way, she’s received the “Rule Breaker Award'' from Billboard Women In Music and performed at?Voodoo Music + More,?Coachella, and beyond. She reached a critical and creative high watermark with her sophomore offering, It Was Good Until It Wasn’t. It not only bowed at #2 on the Billboard Top 200, but it also concluded 2020 on over a dozen year-end lists from Billboard, Esquire, Hypebeast, Nylon, Seventeen, Spin, Stereogum, The Guardian, and many more.
